{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01WMndMzkCYcBjUcHQDFzutf","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me analyze the knowledge file against the source file carefully, checking for omissions, fabrications, section issues, and hints completeness.\n\nLet me go through each section of the source file and compare with the knowledge file.\n\n**Source file sections covered:**\n1. コード値を表示する (code values display)\n2. メッセージを出力する (message output)\n3. 言語毎にリソースパスを切り替える (resource path switching by language)\n4. ブラウザのキャッシュを防止する (browser cache prevention)\n5. 静的コンテンツの変更時にクライアント側のキャッシュを参照しないようにする (static content cache)\n\n\n6. 論理属性を指定する (boolean attributes)\n7. 任意の属性を指定する (dynamic attributes)\n8. 論理属性の扱い (boolean attribute handling - subsection of dynamic attributes)\n9. Content Security Policy(CSP)に対応する (CSP support)\n10. セキュアハンドラが生成したnonceを任意の要素に埋め込む (nonce embedding)\n\nNow I'm checking the knowledge file against these sections to see if all the key content has been captured, looking for any gaps or inaccuracies in how each feature is documented. The codeSelect implementation correctly filters out OTHER when PATTERN2 is 0, which matches the knowledge file examples. I'm verifying that sections s2 through s4 all have their required attributes, code examples, and important warnings intact—language specifications, resource path rules, cache prevention tips, and SSL considerations are all accounted for. I'm verifying the remaining sections now. Section 5 covers static content changes with the deprecation notice and all affected tags accounted for. Sections 6 and 7 are complete, including the note about dynamic attributes for HTML output tags. Section 8 lists the default boolean attributes and CustomTagConfig reference properly. Section 9 describes all three Content Security Policy behavior changes.\n\nNow I'm checking section 10 on embedding nonce in arbitrary elements—the code example, script_tag tips, and meta element guidance are all there. Moving through a more careful verification of each section to catch any potential issues or inaccuracies.\n\nLooking at section 1, the description of `codeSelect` for dropdowns matches the source, and the requirement for `optionColumnName` when using the `$OPTIONALNAME$` placeholder is correctly stated. The code examples check out.\n\nSection 2's explanation of the `var` attribute setting values to scope aligns with how it's used in the source examples. Section 3 accurately describes the language-based resource path switching functionality. I'm not finding obvious fabrications so far.\n\nNow examining the RST section structure—there are several h2-level sections marked with tildes in the source, including ones about displaying code values, outputting messages, switching resource paths by language, and browser caching behavior. I'm verifying the structure of these sections in the knowledge file—they're organized sequentially from s1 to s10, which properly splits out the subsections as their own entries. The section IDs follow the expected format, and checking the content length, even s7 with its explanation about custom tags and dynamic attributes using the DynamicAttributes interface is well over the 50-character minimum, so the content requirements are met.\n\nNow I'm going through the hints completeness for each section. For s1, CodeUtil appears in the hints as expected while CustomTagConfig doesn't, which is correct. Moving through s7, the DynamicAttributes reference is properly captured. In s8, both CustomTagConfig and the dynamicBooleanAttributes along with individual boolean attributes are all accounted for. For s9, the content_security_policy reference from the source is there, and the related tags like form_tag, script_tag, and csp_nonce_tag are included. Finally, s10 has csp_nonce_tag and sourceFormat covered in the hints.\n\nLooking more carefully at s4, the hints do include SSL which matches the source. While IE6, IE7, and IE8 appear in the source but not in the hints, that's acceptable since hints are meant for routing rather than being exhaustive. For s9, content_security_policy itself isn't listed as a hint, but CSP and Content Security Policy are there, which should be sufficient. Reviewing s4 more thoroughly, the source covers cache-related concepts like tag-no_cache_tag, noCache, Cache-Control and Pragma headers, browser cache prevention, and cache control, along with SSL—the hints seem to capture the essential routing information.\n\nNow checking s3, I notice confirmation_page_tag appears in the source as a supported tag for language-based resource path switching, but it's missing from the hints even though the knowledge file references it. That's a potential gap. I should also verify s5's hints, particularly around popup-related content.\n\nActually, looking at the validation rule more carefully—it specifies PascalCase class names, @Annotation names, and property names from tables. Tags like confirmation_page_tag, popup_submit_tag, and download_submit_tag are lowercase snake_case references, not PascalCase class names, so their absence from hints is probably fine. Let me scan through the rest to see if there are any other meaningful omissions I've overlooked.\n\nNow I'm checking the note section for s4. The source includes a tip about browser cache prevention—specifically that it doesn't work in IE6, IE7, and IE8 when using HTTP/1.0 without SSL. The knowledge file captures this same point about requiring SSL for screens that use cache prevention. That's preserved correctly.\n\nLooking at the s3 section more closely, the source references a subsection about default subclasses, but the reference appears to be cut off in the source material itself.\n\nIn s9, I'm noticing a discrepancy with the form_tag description. The source includes \"自動でonclick属性に指定する関数呼び出しを含む\" as clarification about automatically specifying function calls in the onclick attribute, but the knowledge file has simplified this to just \"onclick属性の関数呼び出し含む\" without capturing the \"automatic\" aspect. This might be worth adjusting to be more precise.\n\nFor s5, I've verified the version parameter functionality matches between source and knowledge file, and the condition about when the feature is disabled also checks out. The knowledge file looks solid overall. Let me do a final pass through the codeSelect output section to make sure everything there is accurate too. I've already confirmed the knowledge file is accurate for the gender select options and the code/codeSelect attributes. Now I'm checking the documentation about the no_cache_tag — it mentions that this tag can't be used in JSPs that are included via jsp:include, so it must be specified in forwarded JSPs instead, and there's a note about preventing browser cache at the project level to avoid implementation gaps. ハンドラで設定したレスポンスヘッダが正しく機能していることを確認できた。知識ファイルも検証済みで、特に問題は見当たらない。","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":22136,"cache_read_input_tokens":18400,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":22136,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f0597f85-ac43-4bbd-8397-d427ebf8c145","uuid":"34b54bbc-8c44-4794-b93e-b0cf5877a4de"}
